videos.description: Gonzaga's Nigel Williams-Goss dribbles around and fades away for the jumper to open up the scoring for the Bulldogs.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Williams-Goss hits fadeaway jumper

videos.description: BYU's Elijah Bryant hits a 3-pointer and Gonzaga's Jordan Matthews responds with a 3-pointer for the Bulldogs.
videos.headline: BYU and Gonzaga trade 3s

videos.description: Gonzaga's Johnathan Williams drives and finishes with the one-handed slam over the BYU defender.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Williams slams down dunk

videos.description: BYU's Eric Mika misses the alley-oop dunk and is called for basket interference.
videos.headline: Mika misses alley-oop dunk

videos.description: BYU's Yoeli Childs finishes with the two-handed dunk off the great pass from T.J. Haws.
videos.headline: BYU's Childs with the strong dunk

videos.description: Gonzaga's Johnathan Williams grabs the offensive rebound and draws the foul.
videos.headline: Williams rebounds and gets and-1

videos.description: Gonzaga's Nigel Williams-Goss goes coast-to-coast and finishes with a finger roll to help pad the Bulldog's lead.
videos.headline: Williams-Goss with the transition bucket

videos.description: BYU's T.J. Haws hits consecutive 3-pointers to help bring the Cougars within single digits.
videos.headline: BYU's Haws hits back-to-back 3s

videos.description: Nigel Williams-Goss scores a game-high 33 points as No. 1 Gonzaga defeats BYU 85-75 to improve to 23-0.
videos.headline: Williams-Goss leads Gonzaga past BYU
